Northeast India, with a population of 38 857 769, is the eastern-most region of India connected to the rest of India via a narrow corridor between Nepal and Bangladesh. It comprises 7 contiguous states -- Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland, and Tripura -- and the Himalayan state of Sikkim (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northeast_India). Almost 70 per cent of this population (26.64 million) lives in the state of Assam. The region is predominantly tribal and rural. For a map of the northeast region of India, see http://www.emapsworld.com/images/north-east-india-map.gif. - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/2yW8.]
